    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a scatterplot on the first quadrant of a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “sine of theta sub liquid,” and the numbers 0.0 to 0.8, in increments of 0.2, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “sine of theta sub air” and the numbers 0.0 to 0.8, in increments of 0.2, are indicated. There are 5 data points in the scatterplot. The following values are approximate. The coordinates of the data points are as follows. First point, 0.11 comma 0.11. Second point, 0.19 comma 0.25. Third point, 0.3 comma 0.35. Forth point, 0.39 comma 0.49. The last point, 0.49 comma 0.6.\" src=\"/images/05fa9cd5e0a080d76cbb460bffc6d399.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In an experiment to determine the refractive index of a liquid, an engineer directs a laser beam from the air into the liquid. The engineer measures the angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub air \"><math alttext=\"theta sub air \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>air</mi></msub></math></span></span> in air and the angle of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub liquid\"><math alttext=\"theta sub liquid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>liq</mi></msub></math></span></span> in the liquid for various incident angles. The sines of the angles of incidence and refraction are then calculated and used to make the graph shown in the figure. According to the graph, at approximately what minimum angle of incidence <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">in the liquid</span> would a beam <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">not</span> be transmitted into the air?</p>\n",
